Summary Method for an Object of Class ctmedmed

Source: R/cTMed-methods.R
summary.ctmedmed.Rd

Summary Method for an Object of Class ctmedmed

Usage

# S3 method for ctmedmed
summary(object, digits = 4, ...)

Arguments

object

an object of class ctmedmed.

digits

Integer indicating the number of decimal places to display.

...

further arguments.

Value

Returns a matrix of effects.

Author

Ivan Jacob Agaloos Pesigan

Examples

phi <- matrix(
  data = c(
    -0.357, 0.771, -0.450,
    0.0, -0.511, 0.729,
    0, 0, -0.693
  ),
  nrow = 3
)
colnames(phi) <- rownames(phi) <- c("x", "m", "y")

# Specific time-interval ----------------------------------------------------
med <- Med(
  phi = phi,
  delta_t = 1,
  from = "x",
  to = "y",
  med = "m"
)
summary(med)
#>      interval total  direct indirect
#> [1,]        1  -0.1 -0.2675   0.1674

# Range of time-intervals ---------------------------------------------------
med <- Med(
  phi = phi,
  delta_t = 1:30,
  from = "x",
  to = "y",
  med = "m"
)
summary(med)
